==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Epidote
<hw>Ep"i*dote</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Gr. <?/ to give
besides; <?/ over + <?/ to give: cf. F. <ets>⟦eacute⟧pidote</ets>. So
named from the <ets>enlargement</ets> of the base of the primary, in
some of the secondary forms.]</ety> <fld>(Min.)</fld> <def>A mineral,
commonly of a yellowish green (pistachio) color, occurring granular,
massive, columnar, and in monoclinic crystals. It is a silicate of
alumina, lime, and oxide of iron, or manganese.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><note>⟦hand⟧ The <membof>Epidote group</membof> includes ordinary
epidote, zoisite or <stype>lime epidote</stype>, piedmontite or
<stype>manganese epidote</stype>, allanite or <stype>cerium
epidote</stype>.</note>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Epidotic</ent>⟦br⟧
